Rating: 3
Loved this cookie. After reading all reviews, I made the following changes: (1)Used parchment paper instead of buttering. No mess and I was able to slide the paper and cookies onto cooling racks. (2)Substituted vanilla vodka for the extract, added it to the cherries, which I had chopped, and let it sit while I continued with the other prep work. (3)Toasted the nuts in preheated oven for 5 minutes, then chopped and cooled them. (4)Added 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips, chopped, and left in freezer until used. (5)Spooned flour into measuring cups, then sifted. (6)Thoroughly incorporated flour into butter mixture by hand and then returned to stand mixer for a few pulses to finish the job. (7)Used a small cookie scoop and got about 8 dozen out of the batch. Next week I plan to make these again. But I will substitute cream cheese for some of the butter, cranberries for the cherries, pecans for the pistachios, add a little orange zest and perhaps some white chocolate chips. Can't wait to see how those turn out!

Rating: 4
Excellent. I rubbed the pistachios in a towel to loosen some of the hull and put them in a coarse sieve to remove the powdery stuff. I used dried cherries, chopped, and only one Tbls. vanilla (not big on vanilla). The dough was crumbly, so I formed balls instead of football shapes, worked just fine. Also, I don't like things very sweet, so I only dusted them with powdered sugar after they had cooled on a cooling rack. By the way, instead of buttering baking sheets (messy), use parchment paper. Virtually no clean up!

