These were a nice twist on wedding cookies- since the cherries add some chewiness. I would have to say, though, that based on taste I prefer the traditional wedding cookie with pecans or walnuts. Pistachios are not nearly as flavorful, as others have noted. Overall pros: nice holiday colors with the green/red, very tender cookie, and an interesting change. Cons: a bit time-consuming to make the footballs (although that's a cute shape), not as nutty/toasty tasting as normal wedding cookies. If you do make them, definitely make them smaller than suggested, and if you use salted nuts and butter, just cut the salt in the dough. I had to hand- chop the cherries since the food processor didn't chop them up. Worked for the nuts but not the cherries. The dough is crumbly but I found that it formed together fine when squeezed/ formed into shapes. Nice cookie but for me, not quite as good as the original.

