Unmitigated disaster. There is something totally wrong with the proportions here. These liquified into flat pancakes after 7 minutes in the oven -- even after freezing them solid before baking. I'm a fairly experienced baker, and am shocked at how poorly these hold together. I checked, rechecked & weighed all ingredients, used the specified combo of cake vs AP flour. I verified my oven temp. The only thing I did differently was use Silpat instead of buttered pans. There seems to be way too much butter vs dry ingredients. The only thing I can think of is, maybe they mean to pack the flour into the measuring cups and then sift it? I can't even imagine! I won't try this again, just wanted to warn the innocent!

